cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for structured sequence prediction using conditional normalizing flow based prior and regularization schemes. This work involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques for modeling complex multi-modal conditional distributions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with image and video data, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The regularization schemes proposed in the paper involve neural networks, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of latent variable models and variational autoencoders suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
